Uses of Package
xxl.core.collections.containers

Packages that use xxl.core.collections.containers
xxl.core.collections.bags Contains some bags. 
xxl.core.collections.containers Provides some containers. 
xxl.core.collections.containers.io Provides some containers that are able to store their blocks on disk. 
xxl.core.collections.containers.recordManager Provides a decorator container that is able to store records (of type Block ) which are of different size. 
xxl.core.collections.queues.io The package xxl.core.collections.queues.io provides some implementations of the queue datastructure using special containers (BlockBasedQueue), files (FileStackQueue) or streams (StreamQueue) for storing and receiving the data. 
xxl.core.indexStructures Provides important index structures like B-trees, R-trees, M-trees and bulk-loading-algorithms. 
xxl.core.indexStructures.vLengthBPlusTree Experimental Package for variable length B+tree implementation. 
xxl.core.io Provides classes and routines for system input and output through data streams, serialization, raw i/o and a FAT file system. 
xxl.core.util.reflect This package contains useful utilities that need the reflection mechanisms of java sdk 1.3 or higher (dynamic proxies). 
 

Classes in xxl.core.collections.containers used by xxl.core.collections.bags
Container
          A Container is the interface implemented by all classes that deal with the management of sets of objects.
 

Classes in xxl.core.collections.containers used by xxl.core.collections.containers
AbstractContainer
          An AbstractContainer implements all methods of the Container interface except the central methods get, isUsed, ids, objectIdConverter, remove, reserve, size and update which are abstract.
ConstrainedDecoratorContainer
          The class provides a constained decorator for a container.
Container
          A Container is the interface implemented by all classes that deal with the management of sets of objects.
CounterContainer
          This class decorates a container with a counter functionality and counts every call of an insert, get, update and remove method.
EmptyContainer
          This class provides an empty container.
MapContainer
          This class provides an implementation of the Container interface that internally uses a map to store the (id,*)-elements.
UnmodifiableContainer
          This class provides a decorator for a given container that cannot be modified.
